{
  "texts": [
    "For example, 6 of the 17 test cases it generated covered only a single extra line.",
    "However, in all 17 cases, we manually verified that the generated test did, indeed, cover at least one additional valid corner case, such as an early return and/or special processing for special values such as null and empty list.",
    "The median number of lines of code added by a TestGen-LLM test in the test-a-thon was 2.5.",
    "This is a more realistic assessment of the expected additional line coverage from a single test generated by TestGen-LLM.",
    "Evaluation of LLMs and PromptsThe outcome of the first November Instagram test-a-thon gave us confidence that we had a usable tool in TestGen-LLM."
  ]
}